The Apache Commons Lang library is a popular Java library that provides various utilities for manipulating strings, arrays, and other data types. Here's an example of how you can use it to perform at least five different string manipulations:

```java
import org.apache.commons.lang3.StringUtils;

public class StringManipulations {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // 1. ToUpperCase()
        System.out.println("Original String: Hello, World!");
        System.out.println("To Uppercase: " + StringUtils.toUpperCase("hello world"));

        // 2. ToLowerCase()
        System.out.println("\n\n");
        System.out.println("Original String: HELLO, WORLD!");
        System.out.println("To Lowercase: " + StringUtils.toLowerCase("HELLO WORLD"));

        // 3. Trim()
        System.out.println("\n\n");
        System.out.println("Original String:   Hello World   ");
        System.out.println("Trimmed String: " + StringUtils.trim( "   Hello World   "));

        // 4. Repeat()
        System.out.println("\n\n");
        System.out.println("Original String: Hello")
                + StringUtils.repeat(" World", 2)
                + "!");
        System.out.println("Repeated String: Hello World World!");

        // 5. Split()
        System.out.println("\n\n");
        String originalString = "1,2,3,4,5";
        int delimiter = ',';
        String[] splitArray = StringUtils.split(originalString, delimiter);
        for (int i = 0; i < splitArray.length; i++) {
            System.out.print(splitArray[i]);
            if (i < splitArray.length - 1) {
                System.out.print(", ");
            }
        }
    }
}
```

In this example, we're using the Apache Commons Lang library to perform five different manipulations on strings:

*   ToUpperCase(): Converts a string to uppercase.
*   ToLowerCase(): Converts a string to lowercase.
*   Trim(): Removes leading and trailing whitespace from a string.
*   Repeat(): Repeats a substring for a specified number of times.
*   Split(): Splits a string into an array of substrings based on a delimiter.

These manipulations can be used in various scenarios, such as text processing, data cleaning, or formatting strings according to specific requirements.
